summary: Charlotte Jessop, 14, at the 53rd quarterly Hoenn Championships after six months of radio silence during her gym circuit. Jessop...
caption: Charlotte Jessop, 14, at the 53rd quarterly Hoenn Championships after six months of radio silence during her gym circuit. Jessop was disqualified after ordering her Gardevoir to attack the opposing trainer in what was described as a ‘feral, possessed rage’.  League penalty charges were later dropped after Jessop was diagnosed with a psy-induced illness that would come to be known as 'Embrace Syndrome’, the late stage of a Gardevoir’s empathic bond. This case has been used in the law that would ban Gardevoir from being registered in the League. - Caption used in an Ace Trainer Monthly article detailing pokemon bans throughout League history.

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.

summary: So for work we use picture cards to help us teach the kids, but regular words for most occasions in school often doesn’t...
caption:
So for work we use picture cards to help us teach the kids, but regular words for most occasions in school often doesn’t motivate kids a lot because school is well, school. Even if it’s extra classes, motivation with normal things is often boring. So as an extra, I draw Pokemon and other characters so that we can practice the sentences with and that often helps with motivation and getting them to be louder and more willing to practice.

This one is just one Pochama/Piplup I made. There was an older one I did before that was straight on that I did more from memory and not a reference picture. This one I used a reference picture. Medium is crayon on construction paper.
